President Obama has declared a major disaster in Guam and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts from Tropical Storm Halong. The funding will be available to the territory, local governments, and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation. Kenneth K. Suiso has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made if requested and warranted. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.